ABOUT

  Cantera is a group of programs for X11

COPYRIGHT

  Morten Hustveit 2006, 2007, 2008, 2009, 2010

USE

  Window manager
  ==============

    Press Ctrl-F1 ... Ctrl-F12, Super-F1 ... Super-F12 to select desktop.

    Press Super-1 ... Super-9 to select screen.

  Terminal emulator
  =================

    Use Shift in combination with Up, Down, PageUp, PageDown, Home and End to
    scroll.

    Use the middle mouse button or Shift+Insert to paste the primary selection.

    Press the menu key or the calculator button to pass the current selection
    through $HOME/.cantera/commands/calculate and paste the output.

    Press Shift and the menu key, or Shift and the calculator button, to
    automatically select a math expression to the left of the cursor.

CONFIGURATION

  The path of the configuration files is ``$HOME/.cantera/config''.

  Terminal configuration:

    terminal.history-size <history-size>
    terminal.font <font-path>
    terminal.font-size <font-size>
    terminal.palette <palette>

  Bind a key to a command:

    hotkey.<character> <command>

  Run command at startup:

    menu.init <command>

  Automatically launch commands on primary desktop:

    auto-launch.ctrl-f1 <command>
    auto-launch.super-f12 <command>

  Automatically launch commands on subsequent desktops:

    auto-launch.ctrl-f1.1 <command>
    auto-launch.ctrl-f1.2 <command>

  Example Palettes
  ================

    ANSI colors:

      terminal.palette "000000 1818c2 18c218 18c2c2 c21818 c218c2 c2c218 c2c2c2 686868 7474ff 54ff54 54ffff ff5454 ff54ff ffff54 ffffff" 

    Linux Console (according to gnome-terminal):

      terminal.palette "000000 0000aa 00aa00 00aaaa aa0000 aa00aa aaaa00 aaaaaa 555555 5555ff 55ff55 55ffff ff5555 ff55ff ffff55 ffffff"

    Tango (modified to gray on black):

      terminal.palette "000000 3465a4 4e9a06 06989a cc0000 75507b c4a000 c2c2c2 555753 729fcf 8ae234 34e2e2 ef2929 ad7fa8 fce94f eeeeec"

  Example Hotkeys
  ===============

    hotkey.f "firefox"
    hotkey.b "cantera-term"

  Example Initialization
  ======================

    menu.init "setxkbmap us"
    menu.init "setxkbmap -option terminate:ctrl_alt_bksp"

  Example Auto-launch
  ===================

    auto-launch.ctrl-f5 "firefox"

  Curly braces may be used instead of providing the full name of the key in
  every case:

    menu
    {
      init "setxkbmap us"
      init "setxkbmap -option terminate:ctrl_alt_bksp"
    }
